HEADWORD: Andromeda
<hw>An*drom"e*da</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/, the daughter of Cepheus and Cassiopeia. When bound to a rock and
exposed to a sea monster, she was delivered by Perseus.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A northern constellation, supposed
to represent the mythical Andromeda.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of ericaceous flowering
plants of northern climates, of which the original species was found
growing on a rock surrounded by water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Andromed</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Andromede</ent>⟦br⟧
